title: Drawing, "Study for the Clubhouse of the golf club of Newport", 1893–94
medium: Graphite, pen and red ink, brush and brown, red, light blue, green, and black watercolor, on cream wove paper
markings: Written in red pencil, on the reverse: "published by . . ." Similar to 1941-49-2
signed: In brown ink, below image, at right: Whitney Warren f
inscribed: Below image, in ink:  Section / Scale, one inch = 10 ft.
description: Elevation, executed in delicate watercolor washes, showing the central part of the building and the terrace.  A coach stands at left in front of the elevation of the back part.  Below image, a scale and numerical annotations.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Study for the Clubhouse of the golf club of Newport", 1893–94.
1893–94. Graphite, pen and red ink, brush and brown, red, light blue, green, and black watercolor, on cream wove paper. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1941-49-5.
